divs: sighting detailsmy friend who is a photographer in bangkok, thailand took two consecutive shots of this image while trying out his nikon d4 camera. the second shot was taken at speed shutter 1\125 at f13, lens 16-35 f4g shoot 16mm. the location was a quick access from ploenchit expressway at 9:46am on october 16, 2013. fast moving object from first to the second shot was in a split second because the continuous shot rate of the nikon d4 = 10 frame per second. therefore, shooting two frames so the frame is 1\10 of a second.
